cff-version: 1.2.0
message: "If you use ORBIT in your research, please cite it as below."
type: software
title: "ORBIT: Open Web-Reasoning for Information Retrieval Tasks"
abstract: >
  ORBIT is a data pipeline and training framework for building search-augmented
  language models. It constructs multi-hop QA datasets through four rounds of
  Wikipedia seed extraction, DeepSeek-based question generation, self-verification,
  and external judging, then trains retrieval-augmented agents with GRPO via verl-tool.
authors:
  - family-names: Thakur
    given-names: Nandan
    affiliation: University of Waterloo
    orcid: "https://orcid.org/0000-0001-9752-4555"
repository-code: "https://github.com/castorini/orbit"
license: Apache-2.0
year: 2025
keywords:
  - information retrieval
  - retrieval-augmented generation
  - reinforcement learning
  - web search
  - question answering
  - GRPO
